Click on the header to list all [::BBDB] related pages.  BBDB stands for The Insidious Big Brother Database -- an address book that you can hook into your mail- and newsreader, sync with your Palm, etc.

Here are some BbdbMode related pages:

* BbdbAndMailCrypt -- interfacing with encryption routines
* BbdbCanonicalizeAddresses -- dealing with ever changing addresses
* BbdbConfiguration -- interesting things to do with BBDB
* BbdbCreateRecord -- creating new records your own way
* BbdbFaces -- adding and viewing X-Faces
* BbdbFoaf -- BBDB and Friend Of A Friend interaction
* CategorizingInformationManager -- provides ee-bbdb to browse bbdb records
* [[Icicles - Completion in Other Buffers | Icicles - BBDB Completion]] -- enhanced completion for BBDB


Custom Address Formats

* AddressFormatBrazil -- Brazilian address formatting
* AddressFormatUK - UK address formatting

Mail

* BbdbMailingLists -- how to define a mail alias for a number of people
* AutoCreateBbdbEntries
* BbdbAndGnusAuthorNames
* SplitMailUsingBbdb -- use the BBDB to split mail in Gnus

Importing and Exporting

* BbdbMerging -- merging two databases
* BbdbExportImportSync -- export, import, synchronization (was BbdbSyncWithPalm)
* BbdbImporters -- importing stuff into BBDB
* BbdbExporters -- exporting stuff from BBDB
* BbdbImportFromOutlook -- use to export Outlook contacts to .bbdb
* Other external resources:
** [http://www.mailmeanywhere.org/sw.free/neda/eoe/bbdbFilters/bbdb-filters/accessPage.html BBDB BBDB Input and Output Filters]
** [http://search.cpan.org/search?query=BBDB Perl Packages on CPAN]
